    "body": "## Description\r\n\r\nCloses https://github.com/NVIDIA/cccl/pull/5578\r\n\r\nhttps://github.com/NVIDIA/cccl/pull/4562 added support for \"well-known\" unary and binary operations in the CCCL C library. This PR exposes the same to Python.\r\n\r\nThe usage looks like:\r\n\r\n```python\r\nreduce_into(d_input, d_output, parallel.OpKind.PLUS, len(d_input), h_init)\r\n```\r\n\r\n### Performance\r\n\r\nI investigated `reduce_into` performance on H100 and saw a small, but consistent, perf improvement from using the well-known `PLUS` operator. We expect the speedup to be more dramatic for operations like `scan`, but those are not yet able to reuse the CUB tuning policies (https://github.com/NVIDIA/cccl/issues/4359).\r\n\r\n<details>\r\n<summary> Benchmarking script </summary>\r\n\r\n```python\r\n\r\nimport sys\r\n\r\nimport cupy as cp\r\nimport numpy as np\r\n\r\nimport cuda.bench as bench\r\nimport cuda.cccl.parallel.experimental as parallel\r\n\r\n\r\ndef reduce_pointer(input_array):\r\n    \"\"\"Two-phase reduce operation with custom addition function.\"\"\"\r\n    size = len(input_array)\r\n    res = cp.empty(tuple(), dtype=input_array.dtype)\r\n    h_init = np.zeros(tuple(), dtype=input_array.dtype)\r\n\r\n    def my_add(a, b):\r\n        return a + b\r\n\r\n    alg = parallel.make_reduce_into(input_array, res, my_add, h_init)\r\n    temp_storage_bytes = alg(None, input_array, res, size, h_init)\r\n    temp_storage = cp.empty(temp_storage_bytes, dtype=np.uint8)\r\n    alg(temp_storage, input_array, res, size, h_init)\r\n\r\n    cp.cuda.runtime.deviceSynchronize()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef reduce_pointer_well_known(input_array):\r\n    \"\"\"Two-phase reduce operation using well-known PLUS operation.\"\"\"\r\n    size = len(input_array)\r\n    res = cp.empty(tuple(), dtype=input_array.dtype)\r\n    h_init = np.zeros(tuple(), dtype=input_array.dtype)\r\n\r\n    # Use the well-known PLUS operation from OpKind\r\n    alg = parallel.make_reduce_into(input_array, res, parallel.OpKind.PLUS, h_init)\r\n    temp_storage_bytes = alg(None, input_array, res, size, h_init)\r\n    temp_storage = cp.empty(temp_storage_bytes, dtype=np.uint8)\r\n    alg(temp_storage, input_array, res, size, h_init)\r\n\r\n    cp.cuda.runtime.deviceSynchronize()\r\n\r\n\r\ndef reduce_pointer_bench(state: bench.State):\r\n    \"\"\"Benchmark for reduce_pointer with custom addition function.\"\"\"\r\n    size = state.get_int64(\"size\")\r\n\r\n    # Generate input data\r\n    input_array = cp.random.randint(0, 10, size, dtype=cp.int32)\r\n\r\n    # Add performance metrics\r\n    state.add_element_count(size, column_name=\"Elements\")\r\n    state.add_global_memory_reads(input_array.nbytes, column_name=\"InputBytes\")\r\n    state.add_global_memory_writes(\r\n        input_array.dtype.itemsize, column_name=\"OutputBytes\"\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    # Add summary information\r\n    state.add_summary(\"Operation\", \"Custom Addition\")\r\n\r\n    def launcher(launch: bench.Launch):\r\n        reduce_pointer(input_array)\r\n\r\n    state.exec(launcher, sync=True)\r\n\r\n\r\ndef reduce_pointer_well_known_bench(state: bench.State):\r\n    \"\"\"Benchmark for reduce_pointer_well_known using PLUS operation.\"\"\"\r\n    size = state.get_int64(\"size\")\r\n\r\n    # Generate input data\r\n    input_array = cp.random.randint(0, 10, size, dtype=cp.int32)\r\n\r\n    # Add performance metrics\r\n    state.add_element_count(size, column_name=\"Elements\")\r\n    state.add_global_memory_reads(input_array.nbytes, column_name=\"InputBytes\")\r\n    state.add_global_memory_writes(\r\n        input_array.dtype.itemsize, column_name=\"OutputBytes\"\r\n    )\r\n\r\n    # Add summary information\r\n    state.add_summary(\"Operation\", \"PLUS Operation\")\r\n\r\n    def launcher(launch: bench.Launch):\r\n        reduce_pointer_well_known(input_array)\r\n\r\n    state.exec(launcher, sync=True)\r\n\r\n\r\nif __name__ == \"__main__\":\r\n    # Register reduce_pointer benchmark\r\n    reduce_pointer_b = bench.register(reduce_pointer_bench)\r\n    reduce_pointer_b.add_int64_axis(\"size\", [100000, 1000000, 10000000, 100000000])\r\n\r\n    # Register reduce_pointer_well_known benchmark\r\n    reduce_well_known_b = bench.register(reduce_pointer_well_known_bench)\r\n    reduce_well_known_b.add_int64_axis(\"size\", [100000, 1000000, 10000000, 100000000])\r\n\r\n    # Run all benchmarks on RTX 6000 Ada (Device 0) only\r\n    # Use --device 0 to target the RTX 6000 Ada instead of T400\r\n    sys.argv.extend([\"--device\", \"0\"])\r\n    bench.run_all_benchmarks(sys.argv)\r\n```\r\n\r\n</details>\r\n\r\n```\r\n## [0] NVIDIA H100 PCIe                                                                                                                                                                 \r\n                                                                                                                                                                                        \r\n|    size    |   Ref Time |   Ref Noise |   Cmp Time |   Cmp Noise |      Diff |   %Diff |  Status  |                                                                                   \r\n|------------|------------|-------------|------------|-------------|-----------|---------|----------|                                                                                   \r\n|   100000   |  49.159 us |       7.64% |  46.339 us |       7.31% | -2.819 us |  -5.74% |   SAME   |                                                                                   \r\n|  1000000   |  52.134 us |       3.78% |  49.292 us |       4.65% | -2.841 us |  -5.45% |   FAST   |                                                                                   \r\n|  10000000  |  76.401 us |       2.40% |  73.501 us |       3.19% | -2.899 us |  -3.79% |   FAST   |                                                                                   \r\n| 100000000  | 264.105 us |       5.59% | 262.336 us |      11.77% | -1.769 us |  -0.67% |   SAME   |                                                                                   \r\n| 1000000000 |   2.110 ms |       0.25% |   2.108 ms |       0.15% | -2.147 us |  -0.10% |   SAME   | \r\n```\r\n\r\n\r\n## Checklist\r\n<!-- TODO: - [ ] I am familiar with the [Contributing Guidelines](). -->\r\n- [ ] New or existing tests cover these changes.\r\n- [ ] The documentation is up to date with these changes.\r\n",
