      "merge_method": "squash",
      "commit_title": "`cuda.cccl.parallel`: Expose \"well-known\" operations to Python (#5578)",
      "commit_message": "* Expose well-known ops to Python\n\n* Update algorithms to accept well-known ops\n\n* Update existing tests and examples to use well-known ops\n\n* Add bench_scan.py\n\n* Xfail tests we know will fail due to 5515\n\n* Remove duplicate test\n\n* Pre-commit fixes\n\n* Address some review feedback for bench_reduce.py\n\n* Refactor bench_scan.py after review feedback\n\n* Simplify OpKind enum implementation\n\n* Reference GH#5515 in xfailing test\n\n* Update all examples to use well-known operations\n\n* Remove debug prints\n\n* Fix typing for OpKind\n\n* Undo unnecessary import changes, and move added tests away from the test_*_api.py files\n\n* Also use = for MAXIMUM\n\n* Update existing benchmarks to use well-known ops when possible, add custom ops benchmarks\n\n* Use an IntEnum to implement OpKind\n\n* Fix type annotations for OpKind\n\n* These aren't defined yet\n\n* Comment out the right thing\n\n* Update test_bindings.py\n\n* Remove empty TYPE_CHECKING blocks\n\n---------\n\nCo-authored-by: Ashwin Srinath <shwina@users.noreply.github.com>"
    },
